Subject:Re: [child_lit] Philip Pullman and Neil Gaiman on the BBC
	Talking	Grimm Fairy Tales
Interesting about the girls next door to the Grimms. Feminists often make
the point that the stories were told by woman - often uneducated - and they
left out lots because they were speaking to educated males and felt shy
mentioning things like menstruation and other bodily functions. I've always
been interested in this aspect, so I'd also really like to hear if anyone
else knows anything about the mysterious girls next door! =


