Grimm Fairy Tales

Two lectures I'd love to hear!

I lived briefly just down the road from Hanau, the hometown of the Grimms,
and I loved hunting up different German versions of the tales. It's been a
long time but I do remember, as Philip mentioned in the all too brief
interview, some really good stories that I'd never seen in English. I also
remember some tales that seemed blatantly political. I'd love to learn more
about the politics of the day when the Grimms were writing. Their main
occupation was compiling a German dictionary and grammar, which is in some
respects a political act. The tales were just a sideline that eventually got
more attention than their other linguistic endeavors. =


I also heard from neighbors and librarians in my town that it wasn't the
Grimms at all who collected the fairy tales but the girls who lived next
door who went out and interviewed grandmother-storytellers. But I've never
heard that information in anything I've read about the Grimms since. I'd
love to learn more about that as well. =


It's been great fun to have the Grimm TV show filming here in Portland
although I've sometimes had to reroute my daily hike because they were
filming yet another gruesome murder on my favorite walk.

Rosanne Parry
WRITTEN IN STONE, 2013
SECOND FIDDLE, 2011
HEART OF A SHEPHERD, 2009
www.rosanneparry.com
















